1
00:00:04,630 --> 00:00:07,349
Qualitative assessment.

2
00:00:07,349 --> 00:00:11,843
John Hick, a Christian theologian,

3
00:00:11,843 --> 00:00:17,084
he said Christianity is on the verge
of a Copernican revolution.

4
00:00:17,254 --> 00:00:21,497
[Copernican Revolution of Theism]

5
00:00:21,497 --> 00:00:24,398
Meaning, just like before Copernicus

6
00:00:24,398 --> 00:00:28,990
they thought the Earth is the centre,
it’s a geocentric system,

7
00:00:28,990 --> 00:00:32,607
and the Sun and so many planets
are orbiting the Earth.

8
00:00:32,622 --> 00:00:37,321
Then Copernicus came along
—declared a heretic in the beginning—

9
00:00:37,321 --> 00:00:45,753
saying that actually it’s a solar system;
heliocentric. The Sun is in the centre,

10
00:00:45,753 --> 00:00:49,580
and the Earth is one of many planets
orbiting that Sun.

11
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:53,107
So John Hick,
this Christian theologian, said,

12
00:00:53,107 --> 00:00:56,950
“Christianity is on the verge
of a Copernican Revolution.”

13
00:00:56,950 --> 00:01:02,396
Meaning, “Up to this point we thought
this is the central God conception,

14
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:08,836
and there are so many others
in remote orbit.”

15
00:01:08,836 --> 00:01:11,879
He’s saying, “No.
What you’re about to find out

16
00:01:11,879 --> 00:01:16,324
is this is one of a plurality
of theistic conceptions

17
00:01:16,341 --> 00:01:23,665
orbiting a Central Truth,
a Supreme Reality.”

18
00:01:24,247 --> 00:01:29,996
So then, for those who want
to make a comparative analysis,

19
00:01:29,996 --> 00:01:33,232
somebody could say,
“Well, all are in orbit

20
00:01:33,232 --> 00:01:35,855
and all are planets,
you can find similarities”,

21
00:01:35,855 --> 00:01:39,945
but if someone wants to start
finding a gradation,

22
00:01:40,683 --> 00:01:46,019
then they’ll have to become acquainted
with the central conception,

23
00:01:46,019 --> 00:01:51,699
and then see how it's reflected
into the satellites.

